## 9. SECURITY BEST PRACTICES

### Credential Protection
- ✅ No credentials in Git (all in GSM/Vault/KMS)
- ✅ No credentials in workflow logs (all masked)
- ✅ No long-lived credentials (all ephemeral)
- ✅ Automatic rotation (daily + on-demand)
- ✅ Multi-layer fallback (if one layer fails)

### Access Control
- GitHub OIDC: No stored credentials needed
- Service Accounts: Ephemeral (created per use)
- Token TTL: 15-20 minutes (auto-cleanup)
- Audit Trail: All access logged

### Compliance
- Immutable: All changes tracked in Git
- Auditable: Every action logged to GitHub Issues
- Recoverable: Full history available
- Testable: Can replay any deployment

